external_knowledge:
- "Unique students" refers to the distinct count of students enrolled in a section;
- "Average grade" is calculated by considering null grades as 0 and rounding up to the nearest integer before averaging;
- "Prerequisites" and "co-requisites" are concatenated lists of course IDs for prerequisite and co-requisite courses, respectively.

- 'High-achieving' refers to students with a GPA greater than 3.0;
- 'Specified course' refers to the course with the subject code 'HMCO17G06';
- 'Recent semester' refers to 'Fall 2023'.

- 'HMCO17G06' is the subject code for a specific course;
- 'Fall 2023' refers to a specific semester;
- The average GPA is calculated for students enrolled in the course during the specified semester.

- "sailing through the semester" refers to students who are currently enrolled;
- "navigated the rapids of their prerequisite courses" refers to students who have completed the prerequisites;
- "instructors guiding their current courses" refers to the instructors teaching the courses in the current semester.

- "young minds" refers to students;
- "seeds of wisdom" refers to courses;
- "specific sage" refers to an instructor with a specific ID;
- "particular plot of the educational landscape" refers to a specific course;
- "specific season" refers to a specific semester.

- "garden of academic pursuits" refers to the academic environment or educational institution;
- "blossoms" refers to students;
- "current season" refers to the current active semester (semester_id = 1);
- "plots" refers to sections of courses;
- "seeds" refers to courses;
- "sprouts" refers to students enrolled in the sections.

- "blossoming minds" refers to students;
- "nurturing their interests" refers to taking elective courses;
- "this semester" refers to the current semester (is_current = 1).
